sec.p:
The UP was classified into type 1, in which the UP and the infundibulum are fully developed and defined; type 2, in which there is hypoplasia of the UP and ill-defined infundibulum; and type 3, in which the UP is absent (
Fig. 1
).

caption.p:
Computed tomography scans showing the types of uncinate process (UP); (
A
) type 1, in which the UP and the infundibulum are fully developed and defined; (
B
) type 2, in which there is hypoplasia of the UP and ill-defined infundibulum; and (
C
) type 3, in which the UP is absent.

sec.p:
Then, the UP was evaluated according to its direction in relation to the vertical plane and classified into medialized, vertical, or lateralized (
Fig. 2
).

caption.p:
Computed tomography scans showing different directions of the UP: (
A
) medialized UP; (
B
) vertical UP; and (
C
) lateralized UP.

sec.p:
Then, the pneumatization of the UP was checked (
Fig. 3
), and we evaluated the relation of the pneumatization of present to the nearby pneumatization at the middle meatus area. The relation of pneumatized UP to the deviation of the nasal septum was also registered.
